The paper deals with fitting and segmenting multi-structural data from images, which is a common problem in computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed method involves energy minimization and convex relaxation, which are techniques commonly used in machine learning (cs.LG) and optimization (cs.GR). The paper also mentions the use of different metrics, which suggests a focus on algorithmic design and experimentation (cs.RO). Finally, the paper reports accurate results on publicly available datasets, which is a common evaluation metric in artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
